						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1447 (1526 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged. Records an endowment of 105 <hi rend="italic">poṉ</hi> for maintaining the persons engaged in reciting the <hi rend="bold">Jñānachintāmaṇi</hi> before the god. The details of the date viz., <hi rend="bold">Śaka 144[7], Pārthiva, Makara, ba. 5, Wednesday, ••••• regularly correspond to 1526 A.D. January 3, Wednesday, ·82. The</hi> <hi rend="italic">nakshatra</hi> <hi rend="bold">was Pūram, ·07.</hi></p>						

